title Neth settlement layer — TigerBeetle-as-L2 design, honest naming and scope, grounded in existing WOV/MALA
prompt Keaton proposed an N-vane after Maze called Neth — the Glow OS version of Sui, evolved from MALA, interoperating with Ethereum; MALA as a social experiment of a fractal universe of ETH/SOL/SUI/Azimuth, with an L2 that is a WOV Glow implementation fusing a Glow TigerBeetle reimplementation as a pinned sidechain to a Mala Mycelium/Weave/Mantra/Ford L1 bootstrapped from Neth, woven with a Kumara+Ames fusion and existing Comlink; asked to search first to expand and robustify, then run it with his approval, log to bron + research, commit and push, and print a human-readable overview.
think Searched before forming any opinion. Two findings reframed the whole thing: TigerBeetle is literally a Replicated State Machine (VSR + hash-chained append-only log + deterministic fold), which is architecturally almost exactly an L2 sequencer — so "Glow reimplementation of TigerBeetle as a pinned sidechain" is genuinely coherent, not a buzzword pile. And "Neth" is live Nethermind-ecosystem shorthand (spaceneth, NethDev), a real close-domain collision that bites hardest precisely because Neth's purpose is Ethereum interop.
think Grepped the tree and found the idea is half-built already: MALA is issuer-mint + conservation + balance-as-fold money; WOV is the exit-honesty settlement layer and ALREADY HAD a TigerBeetle pin seam, retired 20260711 but explicitly "revivable later if MALA log-and-fold ever needs TB throughput." Neth is that revival grown up — real continuity, not a cold start. This is the single most important framing: I could affirm the core with confidence because the tree already reasoned to its doorstep.
think Applied the silo discipline to Keaton's own proposal: separated the load-bearing engineering (deterministic RSM produces a pinnable state-root) from the visionary register (the fractal universe of four chains). Recommended NOT building four bridges at once — one anchor, Azimuth/Ethereum, since it is already Urbit's own PKI and needs no new trust — per Gall's Law and the project's own IronBeetle sobriety anchor.
think Gave an honest naming opinion rather than flattering the proposal: the Nethermind collision is real and I lean toward Neith (the weaver goddess, ties to the Weave, though five letters breaks the four-letter vane rule) or another N-name over Neth. Put it on the names checklist as a genuine fork for Keaton, with my lean stated, not decreed.
think Held the financial framing carefully per the external-research rule: marked everything design + social-experiment only, explicitly not financial/investment/legal advice, not a token, not a security, not a deployment. A settlement layer touching real chains carries real stakes if ever deployed; as design it is fine, and I said so plainly rather than letting the crypto framing drift toward advice.
think Recommended a minimal first lap that is one witness, not an L1/L2/bridge: revive the retired WOV-TB pin as a Glow-native fold — sequence a few MALA transfers into a hash-chained log, fold to balances, produce a state-root, prove it is reproducible from the log alone. That single witness proves the load-bearing claim and unlocks the rest without committing to any external chain or any word about real money.
obs Ran the whole turn as design/research — no code, no deployment, no real money, no rename, no history rewrite — consistent with the season's discipline. The proposal's strongest asset is that the tree already walked most of the way to it (WOV-TB pin); the honest cautions are the Nethermind collision and the four-bridge over-reach.
file external-research/20260714-001017_neth-mala-settlement-l1-l2-design.md why: the full architecture, core-vs-vision separation, naming fork, minimal first lap, no-financial-advice framing
file expanding-prompts/20260714-001017_neth-mala-settlement-expanded.md why: the research-grounded expanded form of the seed
file context/specs/20260713-235600_names-awaiting-confirmation.md why: Neth added with the Nethermind collision and Neith/other-name options
recommend check-in — the proposal is affirmed at its core and honestly bounded; the next move is Keaton's word on the Neth name, the single external anchor (recommended Azimuth), and whether to build the one deterministic-root witness as the first lap. Nothing built, deployed, or renamed.
